      • CANTalonMPHandler

        public CANTalonMPHandler(@NotNull
                         RotPerSecCANTalonSRX[] talons,
                         double updaterProcessPeriodSecs,
                         int minNumPointsInBtmBuffer)
        Default constructor.
        Parameters:
        talons - The talons to load profiles into.
        updaterProcessPeriodSecs - The period of the thread in which points are moved from the API-level buffer to the low-level one, in seconds.
        minNumPointsInBtmBuffer - The minimum number of points that must be in the bottom MP buffer to start a profile.

      • isReady

        public static boolean isReady(com.ctre.CANTalon[] talons,
                              int minNumPointsInBtmBuffer)
        Get whether the given talons are ready to start running the loaded profile.
        Parameters:
        talons - The talons the profiles are on.
        minNumPointsInBtmBuffer - The minimum number of points that must be in the bottom MP buffer to start the profile.
        Returns:
        true if all the talons either have at least minNumPointsInBtmBuffer points in the bottom buffer or no points remaining in the API-level buffer, false otherwise.
